Selenium Class 1

What is software testing?
-- identify correctness and quality of the application

How many ways we can actually test?
-- manual
-- automation

When do we go for automation?
-- after manual testing passes
-- when environment is stable
-- analyze our test suite and choose our automation tools

What other tools we have for automation?
 -- Selenium, Cucumber, UFT/QTP, Katalon Studio

 Levels of testing?
-- Unit testing
-- System testing
-- Integration Test
-- Acceptance Test


Types of software testing?
-- Functional testing
-- Non-Functional testing
	Performance testing
	Security testing

What is Selenium?
-- Selenium is a set of tools which helps us to automate web applications. It is mainly used fo functional testing

Selenium Components:
1. Selenium IDE or integrated development environment
2. Selenium RC -> Remote Control
3. Selenium WebDriver
4. Selenium Grid

What is Selenium WebDriver?
Open source automation tool which allows you to perform actions on a web application. WebDriver is an interface.

Advantages of Selenium WebDriver:
-- Open source
-- Works with multiple browsers and supports cross browser testing
-- Works with multiple programming languages --> Java, Ruby, C#, Python, JS
-- OS independent --> iOS, Linux, Windows

Disadvantages Selenium WebDriver:
-- Cannot test Desktop applications
-- No built in reporting
-- No technical support
-- cannot test captchas images
-- takes more time to create test cases

get() vs navigate()
-- get() will wait for the page to fully load whereas navigate() will not
-- get() will not keep the history in your browser whereas navigate() will
-- navigate() will move back and forward, refresh

close() vs quit()
-- close() will close the current tab
-- quit() will close the whole browser
